But we have not found such differences in CERN so far.
Impacts
The impact of such research on our day-to-day is difficult to predict, but we do not believe that we are wrong to say that it will have none.
To see: In the early 1960s, the laser pioneers in the laboratories did not suspect at all the revolution that their work would cause.
They were interviewing scientific applications, but nothing else.
